What is SPF

SPF stands for Sun Protection Factor. It is a measure used worldwide to indicate the level of sunscreen protection. Using an SPF 15 sunscreen means it will take 15 times longer for skin to begin to burn than it would without sunscreen.

Broad Spectrum UVA/UVB

There are two types of ultraviolet (UV) light that can harm your skin- UVA and UVB. A Broad Spectrum sunscreen protects you from both. UVB rays are primarily responsible for causing sunburn while UVA rays are associated with skin aging.

Sunscreen Application

The recommended amount of sunscreen for the average person is 1 Fl Oz. A simple way to remember how much sunscreen to apply is imagine the amount of sunscreen that would fit in a shot glass or the size of a golf ball. Sunscreen should be applied 15 minutes before sun exposure and reapplied every 2 hours or immediately after swimming, sweating or drying off.

Traditional vs Mineral Sunscreens

There are two general types of sunscreen - traditional and mineral. Traditional sunscreens work by absorbing the sun's rays while mineral sunscreens protect skin by blocking the sun's rays. Whichever type you choose, make sure it provides Broad Spectrum UVA/UVB protection.

Product description

Style Name:Mineral Lotion  |  Size:SPF 70

The Australian Gold Botanical SPF 70 Mineral Lotion is more than just powerful sun protection - it's gentle care for your skin. This non-chemical sunscreen lotion delivers non-whitening protection with a refreshingly luxurious, powdery-clean feel. Rich in vitamins and antioxidants from native Australian botanical ingredients, it allows you to enjoy the sun your way, protected from both UVA and UVB rays, and water resistant for up to 80 minutes. Discover the deliciously subtle scents and non-greasy, non-sticky feel of the Australian Gold Botanical Line to look and feel your best every sunny day!

Important information

Ingredients
Titanium Dioxide 3%, Zinc Oxide 3%, Alumina, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter, Caprylyl Glycol, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Cyclopentasiloxane, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Disodium EDTA, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Eucalyptus Globulus Leaf Extract, Fragrance, Glycerin, Hexyl Laurate, Panthenol, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Phenoxyethanol, Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate, Polymethylsilsesquioxane, Porphyra Umbilicalis (Red Algae) Extract, Silica, Squalane, Stearic Acid, Terminalia Ferdinandiana (Kakadu Plum) Fruit Extract, Tocopheryl Acetate, Water, Vitamin E

Directions
Apply liberally 15 minutes before sun exposure. Reapply: After 80 minutes of swimming or sweating, immediately after towel drying, at least every 2 hours. Children under 6 months: Ask a doctor.

How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
Amazon calculates a product’s star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.

SandyTop Contributor: Fountain Pens
3.0 out of 5 stars It has the functionalities that I love but also has the side effects that I dislike
Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2017
Style Name: Tinted Face Mineral LotionSize: SPF 50Verified Purchase
Broke me out and clog my pores. :(

I debated whether to give this three or four stars. It has the functionalities that I love but also has the side effects that I dislike. I have very oily, sensitive skin with enlarge pores and minimal amount of fine lines. I don't wear makeup, I use sunscreen and top with silica powder, brow powder and off I go to work. I did not change anything else in my daily routine.

Pros:
1) Texture is great. It feels like a whipped cream, very light and barely has any scent. Putting it on isn't hard, and no rubbing in involved.
2) Tinted, but not dramatic. The tint is barely there, it can help with light redness and give you a natural look if used alone or a nice base for your makeup.
3) Non-greasy. This is not greasy at all, it dries matte but not dull. Your skin will look very normal.
4) Does not sit in fine lines or pore. It doesn't sink into your pores or fine lines. I have enlarge pores, to the point that you can see my pores easily on a closeup. This doesn't exaggerate my pore at all, in fact it glides over them and blue them out. Of course anything bigger, it won't be able to help.
5) Oil controlling. I used this in an over 10 hour day, humid Boston day. At EOD the sunscreen on my T-zone melted, but that was pretty much it. My oils gave me a natural glow rather than looking like a greasy pit.

Cons:
1) Clog my pores. I used this for a week and exfoliated like I normally would, every Wed and Sun. But I still had non pimple or whitehead bumps everywhere. I also use micellar water to take this product off before using Cetaphil to wash my face. I thought it may be me over washing since Exuviance Daily Protector is very hard to take off so I tone down my exfoliation. That did not work out either.
2) Break outs. Of course break outs are in inevitable after a while. End of the week, I had one or two break outs. They heal quickly but still it's annoying that this gave me break outs.
3) No skin care effects. The product says it has vitamins and antioxidants to help protect the skin. Well let's just say my skin wasn't soft after using this for a week. On top of the clogged pores, there was just nothing that helped my skin.

You may say well there are more pros then cons, I should like it. But I've dealt with acne all my lift. The sight of a pimple annoys me, it makes me feel like all my diligence in keeping my skin clear goes down the drain. I wish this didn't clog my pores. I will use this on and off til I'm done, repurchase is a maybe. I still recommend oily skin guys and gals give this a shot. It's very well priced and it may work for someone else even though it did not work for me.

Se requiere usar un removedor de maquillaje a prueba de agua porque no hay otra manera de quitar este protector solar de la cara. Aun así, con el tiempo tapa y obstruye los poros. Ojo!

Nelly Yazmine Nuñez Reveles
4.0 out of 5 stars Vale la pena probar - precaución piel muy sensible
Reviewed in Mexico on February 21, 2020
Style Name: Tinted Face Mineral LotionSize: SPF 50Verified Purchase
Tiene una consistencia muy fácil de manejar, cubre imperfecciones, acabado mate, es amigable con la reaplicación.

Sus ingredientes son un pro y contra para personas con piel muy sensible. Tiene eucalipto, aunque no es malo, puede ser irritante. En mi caso particular no sé si es este ingrediente o cuál, pero la tolero forma aceptable en la primera aplicación, para las siguientes durante el día ya no, y si la aplico una vez al día en tres días seguidos literalmente no la aguanto y me genera "granitos". No es que los ingredientes sean malos, tiene "iron oxides" y antioxidantes lo cual está muy bien, solo para las personas con piel muy sensible estén concientes que puede ser que no toleren muy bien.

Me parece que si otorga la protección que declara, para lo cual es necesario aplicar la cantidad correcta. En mi caso particular, aplicar una buena cantidad me oscurece la cara y aunque deja un efecto mate mi piel luce sin vida, por lo que estéticamente no me convence.

Sin embargo, por el precio considero que el producto está realmente bien, y aprecio el esfuerzo de hacer estos protectores minerales con color y de mejorarlos.

Habrá muchas personas que les siente de bien a excelente este protector. No me arrepiento de probarlo, lo regalaré a alguien con piel sin problemas de sensibilidad.
